         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/4/92 ¶ After receiving your kind letter this morning, ¶  dear Commandeur Archer, I wrote and sent a letter to the Under Secretary, ¶  pointing out, that I  ¶ recognize ¶   ¶ gratefully ¶   ¶ the kin...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.04.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Henry Archer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">2/137/17, Archer papers, University of Melbourne Archives.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/4/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">After receiving your kind letter this morning,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> dear Commandeur Archer, I wrote and sent a letter to the Under Secretary,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. A deputation from the Royal Society of Victoria met the Chief Secretary on 7 April,</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.5in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">and strongly urged that the sum of money to be set aside for the Government Botanist's department should be increased from £1200 to £1500 a year. Mr. M'Lean remarked that the matter had been carefully considered by the Cabinet before the retrenchment was agreed upon; but in view of the strong representations made by the society he would again bring the matter under the notice of his colleagues (</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 8 April 1892, p. 4).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> pointing out, that I <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">recognize</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">gratefully</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>the kind efforts made by the science-Societies and particularly the Deputation on behalf of my Department, but that I would keep the collections <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">safe</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">under </hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">utilisation</hi>
               </seg> for the £400 left me as working expenses; but that I should feel most thankful if young <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">French</hi>
               </seg> could <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">remain</hi>
               </seg> with me at the additional expense of £128 -. -. annually</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was of course <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not really</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hostile</hi>
               </seg> to the movement on my behalf, but I <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">was</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">afraid</hi>
               </seg>, it was inopportune, as Mr M’Lean and his Colleagues time is just now taken up by the elections extra, — as the new estimates are only framed in May or June, and as I was <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">frighten</hi>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">frightened?</p>
               </note> that the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">discussions</hi>
               </seg> by the Deputation before <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Reporters</hi>
               </seg> might lead to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new expressions</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">against</hi>
               </seg> the Ministry also possible<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">possibly?</p>
               </note> to public suggestion too rashly made. Perhaps you like to send this letter for perusal to our friend Prof Spencer.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. Baldwin Spencer.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
